column10:
+ has several classes;
+ huge variety of spells;
+ spells and classes synergize neatly;
+ probably the flashiest spells of all VS type games;
+ has a rune system to mix things up a bit;
+ long term progression;
+ your runs don't have to be a half hour long.

- late game turns into "endlessly dodge out of the red areas";
- some classes' special abilities become inaccessible late game, for example: I can't fill up the Palladin's special gauge because the enemy is throwing 1000000 grenades in the spot I'm supposed to gather it;
- more expensive than other VS style games;
- gets a bit hard to see at time;
- a bit lackluster in charm and personality.

I spent a good amount of time on it. There's a lot to do and it's nice to take in small sessions between bigger games. I highly recommend it.

[h1]Incredibly addictive without being intrusive, similar to the philosophy of "Deep Rock Galactic"[/h1]

Has a lot of build variety and sinergy, good job of the devs on that one;

A lot of reviews mention "grinding", but honestly in all situations that I can imagine, you would have all resources needed waaay before even unlocking all the characters (which is also very cheap);

Contains a few bugs tough, including major ones. (Ex: Hitboxes having a LOT of phantom range, not being able to craft certain items even with the materials, etc...);

The gameplay is very fast, but doesn't encourage spammy controls, keeping calm and pressing just one button at the right time is all you need.


[b]Overall, needs more updates (which I know they are coming cause of the huge amount of different resources that you don't even have a use at this point), but SOLID and FUN experience.[/b]

Update: They added multiple new weapons that require about 2 hours of non-stop grind to unlock per character, way too much imo.

Update 2: More weapons were added, 2 hours of grind on the hardest difficulty offered won't get you a quarter of one weapon, chill out devs.

Why bad reviews?:{
Most bad reviews are only about the difficulty of the game, i dont think that just being bad at a hard game, is an excuse to 
rate it as not recommended in the review};

Graphics and optimization: {
the game has good optimization and graphics, there are option to change the visibility of your skills (transperancy), this makes the game smoother and easier to play in higher difficulties (Enemies AOE atacks on the ground)};

Soundtrack:
{soundtrack is very "dancy" and eletronic (kinda), keeps it moving like the fast passed gameplay};

The pewpew/dodge dodge:{
The combat is simple and dont need to buy keyboard every 1 week of playing, that's because the game mechanic is auto-fire abilities, this is great, therefore you can focus on dodging and thinking better on which upgrades to get, the game is not hard, but it will be hard if you make the bad choices for your build...};


TLDR{Great game, i recommend it! <3 }.
